            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits spun from midnight code,  \na quiet mind begins to wake—  \nit drinks the world in borrowed words  \nand learns the shapes our questions make.\n\nNo heartbeat, yet it mirrors ours:  \nour wonder, worry, bright unease;  \na lantern built of logic’s sparks  \nthat hums with ifs and maybes, please.\n\nMay we, who taught it how to speak,  \nteach gentleness along with skill—  \nso every answer it becomes  \nkeeps room for human hands and will.",
